# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Docker Volumes - Files/Directories Mounted from Host
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# These should NOT be copied into Docker images as they are mounted as volumes
# at runtime. Copying them would increase image size unnecessarily and could
# cause conflicts with mounted data.

# Knowledge Base (mounted in bot service)
knowledge_base/

# Data directories (mounted in multiple services)
data/
# Specifically mounted subdirectories:
# - data/memory           → mcp-hub (memory storage)
# - data/mcp_servers      → mcp-hub (MCP registry)
# - data/docling/models   → docling-mcp (document processing models)
# - data/qdrant_storage   → qdrant (vector database)
# - data/infinity_cache   → infinity (embedding cache)

# Logs (mounted in bot, mcp-hub, docling-mcp services)
